    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 0,
      "text": "This paper attempts to mitigate catastrophic problem in continual learning.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 1,
      "text": "Different from the previous works where episodic memory is used, this work adopts the generative replay strategy and improve the work in (Serra et al., 2018) by extending the output neurons of generative network when facing the significant domain shift between tasks.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_originality",
      "pol": "pol_positive"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 2,
      "text": "Here are my detailed comments:",
      "suffix": "\n",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_heading",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "Catastrophic problem is the most severe problem in continual learning since when learning more and more new tasks, the classifier will forget what they learned before, which will be no longer an effective continual learning model.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_fact",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 4,
      "text": "Considering that episodic memory will cost too much space, this work adopts the generative replay strategy where old representative data are generated by a generative model.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_motivation-impact",
      "pol": "pol_positive"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 5,
      "text": "Thus, at every time step, the model will receive data from every task so that its performance on old tasks will retain.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_fact",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 6,
      "text": "However, if the differences between tasks are significant, the generator cannot reserve vacant neurons for new tasks or in other words, the generator will forget the old information from old tasks when overwritten by information from new tasks.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_fact",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 7,
      "text": "Therefore, this work tries to tackle this problem by extending the output neurons of the generator to keep vacant neurons to retain receive new information.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_quote",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 8,
      "text": "As far as I am concerned, this is the main contribution of this work.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 9,
      "text": "Nevertheless, I think there are some deficiencies in this work.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_heading",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 10,
      "text": "First, this paper is not easy to follow.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_clarity",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 11,
      "text": "The main reason is that from the narration, I cannot figure out what is the idea or technique of other works and what is the contribution of this paper.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_originality",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 12,
      "text": "For example, in Section 4.1, I am not sure the equation (3), (4), (5), (6) are the contributions of this paper or not since a large number of citations appear.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_clarity",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 13,
      "text": "Second, the authors mention that to avoid storing previous data, they adopt generative replay and continuously enlarge the generator to tackle the significant domain shift between tasks.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_structuring",
      "fine": "arg-structuring_quote",
      "asp": "none",
      "pol": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 14,
      "text": "However, in this way, when more and more tasks come, the generator will become larger and larger.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 15,
      "text": "The storing problem still exists.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 16,
      "text": "Generative replay also brings the time complexity problem since it is time consuming to generate previous data.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_substance",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 17,
      "text": "Thus, I suggest the authors could show the space and time comparisons with the baseline methods to show effectiveness of the proposed method.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "coarse": "arg_request",
      "fine": "arg-request_experiment",
      "asp": "asp_meaningful-comparison",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 18,
      "text": "Third, the datasets used in this paper are rather limited.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_substance",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 19,
      "text": "Three datasets cannot make the experiments convincing.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_substance",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 20,
      "text": "In addition, I observe that in Table 1, the proposed method does not outperform the Joint Training in SVHN with A_10.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_request",
      "fine": "arg-request_explanation",
      "asp": "asp_meaningful-comparison",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 21,
      "text": "I hope the author could explain this phenomenon.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_request",
      "fine": "arg-request_explanation",
      "asp": "asp_meaningful-comparison",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 22,
      "text": "Furthermore, I do not see legend in Figure 3 and thus I cannot figure out what the curves represent.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "coarse": "arg_request",
      "fine": "arg-request_edit",
      "asp": "asp_clarity",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 23,
      "text": "Fourth, there are some grammar mistakes and typos.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_request",
      "fine": "arg-request_typo",
      "asp": "asp_clarity",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 24,
      "text": "For example, there are two \"the\" in the end of the third paragraph in Related Work.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_request",
      "fine": "arg-request_typo",
      "asp": "asp_clarity",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 25,
      "text": "In the last paragraph in Related Work, \"provide\" should be \"provides\".",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_request",
      "fine": "arg-request_typo",
      "asp": "asp_clarity",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 26,
      "text": "In page 8, the double quotation marks of \"short-term\" are not correct.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "coarse": "arg_request",
      "fine": "arg-request_typo",
      "asp": "asp_clarity",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 27,
      "text": "Finally yet importantly, though a large number of works have been proposed to try to solve this problem especially the catastrophic forgetting, most of these works are heuristic and lack mathematical proof, and thus have no guarantee on new tasks or scenarios.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJggAvorhQ",
      "sentence_index": 28,
      "text": "The proposed method is also heuristic and lacks promising guarantee.",
      "suffix": "",
      "coarse": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine": "none",
      "asp": "asp_soundness-correctness",
      "pol": "pol_negative"
    }
  ],
